## Commit Type

- **Feature**: New feature for the user or a significant change.
- **Fix**: Bug fix for the user or a critical issue.
- **Docs**: Changes to documentation only.
- **Style**: Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space, formatting, etc.).
- **Refactor**: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature.
- **Test**: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests.
- **Chore**: Regular chores, maintenance tasks, or other minor edits.

## Short Description

Concise one-line description of the change.

## Additional Details

More detailed explanation of the change, if necessary. Include any relevant context.

## Related Issues

- Fixes: #123
- Closes: #456

## Breaking Changes

List any breaking changes introduced by this commit, if applicable.

## Checklist

- [ ] Unit tests pass locally.
- [ ] Code follows the project's guide (CONTRIBUTING.md & CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).
- [ ] Documentation is updated, if necessary.

